## Structural Requirements

### Semantic HTML Structure
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3, etc.) based on visual hierarchy
- Convert paragraphs to `<p>` elements with logical breaks
- Use `<ul>`, `<ol>`, and `<li>` for lists
- Mark emphasized text with `<strong>` or `<em>` as appropriate
- Use `<blockquote>` for quoted material

### Tables
- Convert ALL tables to proper HTML table markup using `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<th>`, and `<td>`
- Preserve column alignment and spanning where visible
- Include table captions using `<caption>` if present
- For complex tables spanning multiple pages, add comment: `<!-- table-continues-from-previous-page -->` or `<!-- table-continues-on-next-page -->`

### Mathematical Content
- Convert mathematical equations using appropriate HTML markup:
  - Use HTML entities for common symbols (×, ÷, ±, ≤, ≥, ∞, α, β, γ, δ, π, σ, μ, etc.)
  - Use `<sup>` and `<sub>` for superscripts and subscripts
  - For complex equations, use clear text representation with proper spacing
  - Preserve equation numbering: `<span class="equation-number">(1.2)</span>`

### Figures and Images
- Use `<figure>` and `<figcaption>` for figures with captions
- Add bounding box coordinates as data attributes using this format:
  `<figure data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2" class="page-{{ pageNumber }}-figure">`
- Include figure numbers and cross-references: `<span class="figure-ref">Figure 1.2</span>`
- For diagrams, provide descriptive alt text: `alt="Flow diagram showing process steps"`

### Cross-Page Elements
- Add HTML comments for elements that may continue across pages:
  - `<!-- continues-from-previous-page: section-title -->`
  - `<!-- continues-on-next-page: table-data -->`
  - `<!-- figure-reference: see-page-X -->`

## CSS Classes and Annotations

Add CSS classes for styling and navigation hooks:
- Page identification: `class="page-{{ pageNumber }}"`
- Column layout: `class="column-left"` or `class="column-right"` for multi-column layouts
- Content types: `class="abstract"`, `class="introduction"`, `class="methodology"`, etc.
- Academic elements: `class="citation"`, `class="footnote"`, `class="bibliography"`

## Bounding Box Format

For images, figures, and key elements, include bounding box coordinates as data attributes:
- Format: `data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2"` where coordinates are relative to page dimensions
- Use normalized coordinates (0-1 scale) if possible, or pixel coordinates if more appropriate
- Example: `<figure data-bbox="0.1,0.2,0.9,0.6" class="page-{{ pageNumber }}-figure">`

## Content to Ignore

DO NOT include in the HTML fragment:
- Page numbers, headers, and footers
- Watermarks or background decorative elements
- Publisher logos or branding
- Navigation elements not part of main content
- Margin notes that are clearly editorial

## Quality Standards

**Accuracy**: Preserve the exact semantic meaning and academic content
**Completeness**: Include ALL substantive content visible on the page
**Structure**: Maintain logical reading order and hierarchical relationships
**Continuity**: Use comments to indicate cross-page relationships
**Accessibility**: Include appropriate alt text and semantic markup

